Timing Measurement Tool


Overview

This tool is designed for timing measurement in a system using Vulkan and CUDA. It allows for different configurations to analyze timing variations when accessing different numbers of entries in the same hash set.


Requirements

The setup environment remains the same as the Prime Probe tool, requiring:

GCC: gcc-11.4

CUDA: CUDA 12.6

Vulkan: Vulkan 1.2.131


Included Files

The tool consists of the following source files:

dummy.cu

dummy

pointer_chasing_l3.cu

vulkan_buffer.cpp

Makefile


Compilation and Execution

To compile the tool, simply run:

make

This will generate the executable pointer_chasing_l3. To run the tool, execute:

./pointer_chasing_l3


Configuration

Users can modify the following parameters in pointer_chasing_l3.cu:

L3_ENTRY_NUM: Determines the number of entries accessed in the same hash set.

START_SET and END_SET: Define the hash set range for pointer chasing.


Usage with Prime Probe Tool

dummy represents the scenario where zero entries are accessed.

By changing L3_ENTRY_NUM and running the Prime Probe Tool on another virtual machine, users can measure the timing impact of accessing different numbers of entries in this virtual machine.


